        <p>Goa A Strip Of Land 110Kms. Long And 60Kms. Wide, Between The Sahyadri Range Of The Western Ghats And The Arabian Sea On The West Coast Of India. The Coastline Is Indented By Numerous Deep, Sheltered River Estuaries Which Account For The Importance Of Goa’s Harbours On Ancient Trade Routes. The Climate Is Tropical With A June To September Monsoon, When Rainfall Is Approximately 400Cms. For The Rest Of The Year Humidity Is Surprisingly Low And Average Daily Temperature Is 27°C (85°F). The Coolest Months Are November To February When Night Temperat Ures Can Fall To 20°C (70°F) And A Pull-Over May Be Worn.
